<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n38062d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n38" href="#n38062d">N38 (VI.B.32)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n38all.htm#n38062d"> 62(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> a green <font color="green">[thought]</font> / in a green shade </blockquote> <dd class="well"><mm class="note">Note: Andrew Marvell, &lsquo;The Garden&rsquo;: &ldquo;Reducing all that&apos;s mortal made / <mark>To a green thought in a green shade</mark>.&rdquo; The phrase is well-known enough to be used casually by newspapers in any appropriate context. </mm> </dd></dl>
